    "description": "We at Fortis Healthcare Global Group are looking for an experienced Radiologist based out of Mysuru. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Fortis Healthcare Global Group:\nFortis Healthcare Global Group is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Referral bonus program\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Fortis Healthcare Global Group!",
